<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 8:28AM CDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Will,
central Grundy and northwestern Kankakee Counties through 900 AM
CDT...
At 827 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mazon, or near Morris, moving east at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bourbonnais, Braidwood, Wilmington, Coal City, Diamond, Gardner,
Lakewood Shores, Mazon, Braceville, Essex, South Wilmington, Godley,
Carbon Hill, Verona, Wilton Center, East Brooklyn, Kinsman and
Symerton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
